body:
## Context
From PR #289 code review finding.

## Problem
`NewClient` accepts `tokenStore *auth.TokenStore` without validation. If constructed with nil (misconfiguration or future refactor), calling `Submit`/`List`/`Get` will panic on `c.tokenStore.Load()`.

## Current State
The client is only constructed when `platformMode && tokenStore != nil` in main.go, so this doesn't panic in practice.

## Proposed Solution
Change `NewClient` signature to return `(*Client, error)` and validate:
```go
func NewClient(baseURL string, tokenStore *auth.TokenStore, opts ...ClientOption) (*Client, error) {
    if tokenStore == nil {
        return nil, fmt.Errorf("tokenStore is required")
    }
    // ...
}
```

## Priority
Low - defensive improvement, not a bug in current usage.
